<html xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:x="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:excel" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><head><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml><x:ExcelWorkbook><x:ExcelWorksheets><x:ExcelWorksheet><x:Name>Worksheet</x:Name><x:WorksheetOptions><x:DisplayGridlines/></x:WorksheetOptions></x:ExcelWorksheet></x:ExcelWorksheets></x:ExcelWorkbook></xml><![endif]--></head><body><table>   <thead> <tr> <th aria-label="Rk" data-stat="ranker" scope="col" class="ranker poptip center" data-tip="Rank">Rk</th> <th aria-label="Player" data-stat="name_display" scope="col" class=" poptip sort_default_asc center">Player</th> <th aria-label="Age" data-stat="age" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="As of June 30 of the season in question.">Age</th> <th aria-label="Pos" data-stat="team_position" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Position">Pos</th> <th aria-label="WAR" data-stat="b_war" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Wins Above Replacement for position players&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;A single number that presents the number of wins the player added&lt;br&gt;to the team above what a replacement player (think AAA or AAAA) would add.&lt;br&gt;Scale: 8+ MVP Quality, 5+ All-Star Quality, 2+ Starter,&lt;br&gt;0-2 Reserve, &lt; 0 Replacement Level &lt;br&gt; Developed by Sean Smith of BaseballProjection.com" data-filter="1" data-name="">WAR</th> <th aria-label="G" data-stat="b_games" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Games Played">G</th> <th aria-label="PA" data-stat="b_pa" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Plate Appearances&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;When available, we use actual plate appearances from play-by-play game accounts&lt;br&gt;Otherwise estimated using AB + BB + HBP + SF + SH,&lt;br&gt;which excludes catcher interferences.&lt;br&gt;When &lt;span class=tooltip&gt;this color&lt;/span&gt; click for a summary of each PA.">PA</th> <th aria-label="AB" data-stat="b_ab" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="At Bats">AB</th> <th aria-label="R" data-stat="b_r" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Runs Scored">R</th> <th aria-label="H" data-stat="b_h" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Hits">H</th> <th aria-label="2B" data-stat="b_doubles" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Doubles">2B</th> <th aria-label="3B" data-stat="b_triples" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Triples">3B</th> <th aria-label="HR" data-stat="b_hr" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Home Runs">HR</th> <th aria-label="RBI" data-stat="b_rbi" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Runs Batted In">RBI</th> <th aria-label="SB" data-stat="b_sb" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Stolen Bases">SB</th> <th aria-label="CS" data-stat="b_cs" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Caught Stealing">CS</th> <th aria-label="BB" data-stat="b_bb" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Bases on Balls/Walks">BB</th> <th aria-label="SO" data-stat="b_so" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Strikeouts">SO</th> <th aria-label="BA" data-stat="b_batting_avg" scope="col" class=" poptip hide_non_quals center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Hits/At Bats&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;For recent years, leaders need 3.1 PA&lt;br&gt;per team game played&lt;br&gt;Bold indicates either highest BA using current stats&lt;br&gt;or awarded title at end of year." data-filter="1" data-name="">BA</th> <th aria-label="OBP" data-stat="b_onbase_perc" scope="col" class=" poptip hide_non_quals center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;(H + BB + HBP)/(At Bats + BB + HBP + SF)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;For recent years, leaders need 3.1 PA&lt;br&gt;per team game played" data-filter="1" data-name="">OBP</th> <th aria-label="SLG" data-stat="b_slugging_perc" scope="col" class=" poptip hide_non_quals center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Total Bases/At Bats or &lt;br&gt;(1B + 2*2B + 3*3B + 4*HR)/AB&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;For recent years, leaders need 3.1 PA&lt;br&gt;per team game played" data-filter="1" data-name="">SLG</th> <th aria-label="OPS" data-stat="b_onbase_plus_slugging" scope="col" class=" poptip hide_non_quals center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;On-Base + Slugging Percentages &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;For recent years, leaders need 3.1 PA&lt;br&gt;per team game played" data-filter="1" data-name="">OPS</th> <th aria-label="OPS+" data-stat="b_onbase_plus_slugging_plus" scope="col" class=" poptip hide_non_quals center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;OPS+&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;100*[OBP/lg OBP + SLG/lg SLG - 1]&lt;br&gt;Adjusted to the player&amp;#x2019;s ballpark(s)">OPS+</th> <th aria-label="rOBA" data-stat="b_roba" scope="col" class=" poptip hide_non_quals center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;rOBA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;A measure of a player's offensive contributions, weighted in proportion to each event's actual run value" data-filter="1" data-name="">rOBA</th> <th aria-label="Rbat+" data-stat="b_rbat_plus" scope="col" class=" poptip hide_non_quals center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Rbat+&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Batting runs as computed for WAR, but indexed to the environment the player played in, where 100 is league average.">Rbat+</th> <th aria-label="TB" data-stat="b_tb" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Total Bases&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Singles + 2 x Doubles + 3 x Triples + 4 x Home Runs.">TB</th> <th aria-label="GIDP" data-stat="b_gidp" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Double Plays Grounded Into&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Only includes standard 6-4-3, 4-3, etc. double plays.&lt;br&gt;First tracked in 1933.&lt;br&gt;For gamelogs only in seasons we have play-by-play, we include triple plays as well.&lt;br&gt;All official seasonal totals do not include GITP's.">GIDP</th> <th aria-label="HBP" data-stat="b_hbp" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Times Hit by a Pitch">HBP</th> <th aria-label="SH" data-stat="b_sh" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="Sacrifice Hits (Sacrifice Bunts)">SH</th> <th aria-label="SF" data-stat="b_sf" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Sacrifice Flies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;First tracked in 1955.">SF</th> <th aria-label="IBB" data-stat="b_ibb" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Intentional Bases on Balls&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;First tracked in 1955.">IBB</th> <th aria-label="Pos" data-stat="pos" scope="col" class=" poptip center" data-tip="&lt;strong&gt;Positions Played&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The positions either followed by the games played at that position&lt;br&gt; or in order of games or innings played.&lt;br&gt;For a single season, &lt;strong&gt;*&lt;/strong&gt; indicates they played at least 2/3rds of the team games there.&lt;br&gt;Positions after &lt;/strong&gt;/&lt;/strong&gt; indicate less than ten games played at those positions.&lt;br&gt;For career, a + sign means more than 300 games at that position and&lt;br&gt;a - sign means less than 30 games.&lt;br&gt;'H' indicates games as a pinch-hitter or pinch-runner.">Pos</th> <th aria-label="Awards" data-stat="awards" scope="col" class=" poptip sort_default_asc center">Awards</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody><tr data-row="0"> <th scope="row" class="right " data-stat="ranker" csk="9">1</th> <td class="left " data-append-csv="kellyca02" data-stat="name_display" csk="Kelly,Carson-1">Carson Kelly</td> <td class="right " data-stat="age">30</td> <td class="left " data-stat="team_position" csk="1">C</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_war" csk="3.55">3.6</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_games">111</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_pa">421</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_ab">369</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_r">48</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_h">92</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_doubles">13</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_triples">1</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_hr">17</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_rbi">50</td> <td class="right " data-stat="b_sb">2</td> <td 